    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000, 9100, 9200, 9400, AND 9900 MODELS - HEATER AND AIR
        CONDITIONER - TROUBLESHOOTING - Heater-Bunk With Thermostat Temperature Control With Pro Sleeper
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Heater-Bunk With Thermostat Temperature Control With Pro Sleeper</title>
        <table id="t0806308" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Heater-Bunk With Thermostat Temperature Control With Pro Sleeper</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.73in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.90in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.28in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (592). Move key switch to ignition position and move bunk heater
                                blower switch to low. At harness connector, measure voltage from term. A to gnd.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(592), term. A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75AL, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At harness conn. (592) measure voltage from terminal A to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(592), term. A to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 75-GS to sleeper gnd. stud or 11-GAN to
                                B-pillar ground stud, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (162). Measure resistance from (592) term. B to (162) term. B.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(592), term. B to (162) term. B.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 75K, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (162). Measure resistance from (592) term. B to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(592), term. B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Approx. 8K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or short in circuit 75K or the flat pack, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (592). Disconnect sleeper A/C ON/OFF switch (905). At harness to
                                connector (905), measure voltage between pins A and C while turning control knob full
                                CCW, then fully CW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(905), term. A to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Full CCW: A higher voltage. Full CW: A lower voltage.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective automatic temperature control module.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Set control knob to center of range. At connector to switch (905), measure voltage
                                between pins A and C. Does output voltage change as warm or cool air is applied to the
                                ambient air sensor?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(905), term. A to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Varying voltage.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective automatic temperature control module.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install switch (905). Move key switch to ignition position. Measure voltage from
                                (162) term. A to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(162) term. A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75L, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (162). Does heater box damper door function properly?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Sleeper control circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Open top of heater box. Disconnect heater box damper connector (N/L) and with key
                                switch in ignition position, measure voltage from circuit 75L to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(N/L), 75L to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75L, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At heater box damper connector (N/L), measure voltage from circuit 75L to 75-GL.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(N/L), 75L to 75-GL.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 75-GL, conn. (161), circuit 75-G or 11-G to
                                right dash panel gnd. stud, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At heater box damper conn. (N/L), measure voltage from circuit 75K to ground while
                                rotating sleeper temperature control fully CCW and CW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(N/L), 75K to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Approx. 2V and 11V.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75K, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect heater box damper connector (N/L), move key switch to ignition position and
                                note if damper door closes completely and opens completely, when the sleeper temperature
                                control is moved fully CW and CCW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective damper motor assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Sleeper temperature control circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
